The WebGL rain/water effect in this directory (raindrops.js, rain-renderer.js,
gl-obj.js, webgl.js, util.js, shaders/*.vert, shaders/*.frag, assets/*.png) is
vendored and adapted from:

    Rain & Water Effect Experiments by Lucas Bebber
    https://github.com/codrops/RainEffect
    Article: http://tympanus.net/codrops/?p=25417

Original license, from the Codrops repository README:

    "Integrate or build upon it for free in your personal or commercial
     projects. Don't republish, redistribute or sell 'as-is'."

    Full Codrops license terms: http://tympanus.net/codrops/licensing/

This project (ABERP-site / ABENERP) integrates the effect into a SvelteKit
landing page. The original source has been adapted to:

  - run as ES2015 modules (no Browserify/Gulp bundle)
  - inline shaders as strings (no glslify build step)
  - bundle textures via Vite asset URLs (no runtime /img path)
  - drop the weather-slideshow / parallax / lightning-flash code paths
  - expose an initRain(canvas) / destroy() API for SPA mounting
  - remove the GSAP and core-js runtime dependencies

Per the license terms above, this is permitted integration, not republication.
The vendored adaptation is not offered as a standalone library.
